    <p class="style13" 
        style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        &nbsp;</p>
    <p class="style13" 
        style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        The Department of Geology introduced recently in July, 2013 with the first batch 
        of B.Sc. Degree Course in Geology. The primary objective of the Department of 
        Geology is to impart the basic knowledge of Geology to the students.</p>
    <p class="style13" 
        style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        Geology is defined as &quot;the scientific study of the origin, history, and 
        structure of the Earth.&quot; The scope of&nbsp;Geology&nbsp;is very vast and vital to the 
        human lives on this planet. It is difficult to imagine the modern civilization 
        without the resource geological inputs of coal, petroleum, gas, metals 
        and&nbsp;industrial materials. Besides, the&nbsp;internal and external&nbsp;geological 
        processes of the earth have been responsible for the present day landforms. The 
        awareness of the geological hazards like earthquakes, volcanoes, landslides and 
        floods have also made the lives of modern man more safe.</p>
    <p class="style13" 
        style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        Geology is of great importance in the field of Civil Engineering, Mining, 
        Petroleum and Natural Gas etc. The Department of Geology is mainly focus on 
        Physical Geology, Mineralogy, Petrology, Structural Geology, Stratigraphy, 
        Palaeontology, Engineering and Environmental Geology to impart the basic 
        understanding of Geology to the students. The Department has well equipped 
        laboratory and museum with proper arrangement of geological samples (rocks, 
        minerals &amp; fossils), models, charts etc to understand the theory and concept of 
        Geology in an easy way. The departmental library of Banasthali University (Bhu 
        Mandir Library) has very good collections of Geology books to fulfill the 
        requirement of each student.</p>
    <p class="style13" 
        style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
        The Faculty member of the Department is currently engaged in personal research 
        activities in a wide range of research topics such as Quaternary Geology, 
        Sedimentology, Micropalaentology and Palaeoclimatic studies of the Great Rann of 
        Kachchh, Gujarat funded by the SERB (DST), New Delhi.</p>
